subject: FEDERAL RESERVE BANK OF NEW
body:
FEDERAL RESERVE BANK OF NEW YORK
ADDRESS: 33 LIBERTY STREET,
NEW YORK, N.Y 10038.
ATTN: FUND BENEFICIARY,
                  Re: ATM Card payment notification.
This is to officially inform you that the bank Federal Reserve Board
New York Branch  has concluded in the meeting today over your long
overdue contract payment and agreed that your payment worth
US$10.500,000.00 will be released to you through ATM Master Card which
will be delivered to you directly to your home address.
However, you are further advised to know that all arrangement has been
completed long ago for the immediate dispatch to your residency, you
have to reply back to us as soon as possible with the below DATAâ€™ to
enable the Ups shipping department proceed with the immediate dispatch
next tomorrow been Monday dated 3rd of April 2023 on your behalf.
Finally, this is very urgent and important the bank are waiting to
hear from you right away today, Bear in mind that the tracking number
of your parcel will be given to you immediately the Processing charge
and Stamp fee which will not cost you much is received to avoid any
immediate STOP ORDER from the United Nation office.
Note That Because Of Impostors, We Hereby Issued You Our Code Of
Conduct, Which Is (ATM-2023) So You Have To Indicate This Code When
replying back to us By Using It As Your Subject. Get back to us with
this information needed,
Full Names:
Your Address:
Country:
Direct Number:
Your Age And Occupation:
A scan copy of your ID card or passport:
Reply back to us accordingly; The bank Wait For Your Expedite Response.

Mr. Jerome H. Powell
Chairman Federal Reserve Board New York

federalreservebank@iname.com

subject: Re:   FEDERAL RESERVE BANK OF NEW
body:
Hello Mr. Jerome H. Powell,

Thank you for reaching out to me and informing me about this exciting opportunity. I am thrilled to hear that the Federal Reserve Board New York Branch has concluded a meeting regarding my overdue contract payment.

I understand that an ATM Master Card will be delivered to my home address, which is quite convenient for me. However, I have a few questions before we proceed further.

Firstly, could you please provide more details about the processing charge and stamp fee? How much would it cost exactly? 

Secondly, you mentioned a STOP ORDER from the United Nations office. Could you elaborate on what circumstances might lead to such an order?

Lastly, could you explain more about the Code of Conduct ATM? Is it something I need to remember or use frequently?

Looking forward to your response.

Best wishes,
Oscar
